 learned form in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Old German: Mighty battle maid"]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":105,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":114,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Matilda was born in 1110, in England. She had at least 1 son with Simon De Routh."},"et":{"Cir 1110–":"1110–Surnud","1108–Male":"1108–Surnud","1139–1197":"1139–1197","1110–Female":"1110–Surnud","1139":"1139","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1110":"1110","1197":"1197","Cir 1110":"1110","1108":"1108","England":"England","Watton, Yorkshire, England":"Watton, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"Cir 1110–":"1110–Kuollut","1108–Male":"1108–Kuollut","1139–1197":"1139–1197","1110–Female":"1110–Kuollut","1139":"1139","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1110":"1110","1197":"1197","Cir 1110":"1110","1108":"1108","England":"England","Watton, Yorkshire, England":"Watton, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"Cir 1110–":"1110–Décédée","1108–Male":"1108–Décédé","1139–1197":"1139–1197","1110–Female":"1110–Décédée","1139":"1139","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1110":"1110","1197":"1197","Cir 1110":"1110","1108":"1108","England":"Angleterre","Watton, Yorkshire, England":"Watton, Everwyck, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Matilda est née en 1110, à Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 1 fil